translated:
HENKE, Hans Agne Jerker, Director, Nockeby, born in Malmö on May 1, 1902, son of General Consul Hans E H and Esther Forsberg, married to Gunnel Velander. Saltsjöbaden com. school, HHS Berlin. Reserve Officer 1924, Second Lieutenant in the Life Grenadier Regiment 1924, Lieutenant 1927, Lieutenant in the Life Regiment of Horse 1928, Captain 1939. Employed at AB Elektraverken since 1929, AB Osram-Elektrav since 1930, director since 1932. Consul of Latvia in 1938. Board member of AB Feith's coffeehouses and confectioneries 1924-1928, Swedish Association for Lighting Culture 1937-1941, Gropptorp's Marble AB in Katrineholm since 1937, board deputy of AB Osram-Elektrav since 1932, FERA since 1937, chairman of the 1902 Men's Association since 1941, Osram-Elektrav Sports Club since 1932, Stockholm Home Guard from 1943 (vice chairman 1940-1942), club member and treasurer of Swedish-Latvian Association from Stockholm since 1932, secretary 1932-1933 and since 1941, club member of the Royal Motorboat Club since 1936, chairman of its volunteer department since 1936 and local committee member for club matters since 1941, scout leader in Saltsjöbaden 1923-1927. Travel: England, Germany, Switzerland, Austria, Belgium, France 1924-1929, USA 1928, 1929, 1939. Recipient of the Royal Order of Vasa, Swedish-Norwegian Motor Association, Latvian Knight's Cross of the Order of the Cross of Terra Mariana, Officer of the Latvian Order of the Three Stars, Swedish Scout Federation's Silver Medal and White Star, Osram-Elektrav Sports Club's Gold Medal, shooting medal, military sports medal, pistol shooting medal, skiing medal, swimming medal, etc.

HENNEL, Per, Merchant, Kristianstad, born in Linneryd, Kronoberg County on January 29, 1887, married to Stina Lindbladh. Shop assistant at P J Karlsson's Sons in Skruv 1905-1918, co-owner since 1919-1929. Took over Axel Ljungberg's specialty store in Kristianstad and became co-owner with Per Hennel in 1929. Board member of Skruvs Nya Glasbruk AB, founded in 1910.

structured.name: Hans Agne Jerker Henke
structured.description: Hans Agne Jerker Henke was a Swedish Director. He was born on May 1, 1902, in Malmö. His parents were Hans E H Henke and Esther Forsberg. He was married to Gunnel Velander. Hans Agne Jerker Henke attended Saltsjöbaden Community School for his secondary education. He worked as a Director for AB Elektraverken starting in 1929 and for AB Osram-Elektrav starting in 1930. Throughout his career, he was affiliated with various organizations, including AB Feith's Coffeehouses and Confectioneries (1924-1928), Swedish Association for Lighting Culture (1937-1941), Gropptorp's Marble AB (1937-present), AB Osram-Elektrav (1932-present), FERA (1937-present), 1902 Men's Association (1941-present), Osram-Elektrav Sports Club (1932-present), Stockholm Home Guard (1943-present), Swedish-Latvian Association from Stockholm (1932-present), and Royal Motorboat Club (1936-present).
